##6. Connecting the services — end-to-end AWS data pipeline

##•	Explain the role of each IAM policy in the pipeline — what would break if each was removed.
## The following are the IAM Policies. 
##Lambda IAM Policy
##Glue IAM Policy
##Redshift IAM Policy
##SNS IAM Policy


--1. Lambda IAM Policy

--Here, Lambda needs permission to - read S3 file metadata, start Glue job, publish SNS alert and write CloudWatch logs

--These are the required permissions to go ahead.
{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": [
    "s3:GetObject",
    "s3:ListBucket",
    "glue:StartJobRun",
    "sns:Publish",
    "logs:CreateLogGroup",
    "logs:CreateLogStream",
    "logs:PutLogEvents"
  ],
  "Resource": "*"
}

-- If these are removed, the following will break.

-- Lambda can't read file metadata, can't trigger Glue.
-- Lambda can't send SNS alerts and Lambda logs may not appear in CloudWatch.


--2. Glue IAM Policy

--Glue needs permission to - read the raw claims files, write cleaned Parquet files
--Access Glue Data Catalog and write logs to CloudWatch

--These are the required permissions to go ahead.
{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": [
    "s3:GetObject",
    "s3:ListBucket",
    "s3:PutObject",
    "glue:GetDatabase",
    "glue:GetTable",
    "glue:UpdateTable",
    "logs:CreateLogGroup",
    "logs:CreateLogStream",
    "logs:PutLogEvents"
  ],
  "Resource": "*"
}
-- If these are removed, the following will break.

-- Glue can't read raw files, can't write cleaned files.
-- Glue can't access Data Catalog metadata and Glue job logs may not appear.

--3. Redshift IAM Policy

--This needs permission to Read the cleaned files from S3 nad load data using COPY

--These are the required permissions to go ahead.
{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": [
    "s3:GetObject",
    "s3:ListBucket"
  ],
  "Resource": [
    "arn:aws:s3:::healthcare-datalake",
    "arn:aws:s3:::healthcare-datalake/cleaned/*"
  ]
}
-- If these are removed, COPY command will fail, Redshift can't load any cleaned files.
-- stg_claims will remain empty and Analysts will see missing data.

--4. SNS IAM Policy

--SNS allows pipeline alerts to reach the data team.

-- Required permission
{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": [
    "sns:Publish"
  ],
  "Resource": "arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:123456789:data-alerts"
}

-- If removed, validation failures will occur silently, no email alert is sent.
-- Data team may not know the pipeline failed.


--Conclusion:

--Lambda uses IAM to validate files and trigger Glue.
--Glue uses IAM to read raw and write cleaned data.
--Redshift uses IAM to read cleaned data.
--SNS uses IAM to send alerts.
--CloudWatch uses IAM to store logs.